pr_title: Bayesian Excess Variance (Bexvar) in Stingray - GSoC'22 project
pr_body:
This is the base code for implementing Bayesian Excess Variance (bexvar) in Stingray (#582). 

This project is part of Google Summer of Code 2022, a brief summary of the project can be found [here](https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/programs/2022/projects/rG1XqJqK).

pr_title: Add find_bexvar() method in Lightcurve class and its relevant tests - GSoC"22
pr_body:
Added `bexvar()` method in Lightcurve class and its relevant tests as a part of GSoC"22 project.

- Added three new parameters and attributes in the `Lightcurve` class: `bg_counts`, `bg_ratio`, `frac_exp`
- Added `bexvar()` method to find Bayesian excess variance of Stingray `Lightcurve` object
- Added relevant tests to test_lightcurve.py
